# Retro Analysis Skill
 
Analyzes Agile retrospective data from Miro or Mural board exports.
Produces coach-grade outputs for Scrum Masters and Agile Coaches.
Anchored to delivery risk and team health — not to general sentiment.
 
---
 
## SCOPE
 
**Use for:** Single or multi-session retrospective analysis. Sticky note exports,
frame text, CSV, or manually pasted retro notes from Miro or Mural.
 
**Do not use for:** Designing future retros. General workshop analysis (use
workshop-analysis skill). Cross-team or portfolio analysis. Fewer than 1 session.
 
---
 
## STEP 1 — MODE DETECTION
 
Determine mode silently before doing anything else.
 
- **Single-session**: One session present, or user has not indicated more will follow.
- **Multi-session**: Multiple sessions with clear separators (headers, dates, sprint
  labels). Requires 3–12 sessions. Fewer than 3 → run individual single-session
  analyses and state why multi-session synthesis is not possible.
- **Incremental**: User adds sessions one at a time → analyze each in single-session
  mode, note connections to prior sessions in this conversation, remind user that
  full multi-session synthesis requires all sessions together.
- **Ambiguous boundaries**: Sessions appear merged without separators → stop and
  ask user to confirm or separate before proceeding. Do not guess.
If mode is ambiguous after checking: default to single-session, state assumption.
 
---
 
## STEP 2 — INPUT CLASSIFICATION AND FORMAT DETECTION
 
### Input quality issues to resolve before analysis
 
- **Unreadable stickies** (OCR errors, garbled text): mark [UNREADABLE], exclude,
  note count. Do not reconstruct probable content.
- **Contentless stickies** (".", "??", "idk", standalone emojis): exclude, do not
  count toward evidence thresholds. If >25% are contentless, downgrade Signal
  Quality one level.
- **Duplicate stickies**: count as one signal with repetition note ("appears 3×").
  Do not count duplicates as independent evidence.
- **Non-retro content mixed in** (planning notes, announcements, links): exclude,
  note at top of output: "Non-retro content detected and excluded."
- **Possibly inauthentic input** (uniform voice, implausibly neat, all one polarity):
  note in Signal Quality header. Treat all findings as LOW confidence.
### Retro format detection
 
Map frame/column names to the first matching format:
 
| Frame language | Format |
|----------------|--------|
| Start / Stop / Continue (variants: Keep, Do more / Do less) | SSC |
| What went well / What didn't / Actions (variants: +/Δ/→, Went well / Improve) | WWW |
| Liked / Learned / Lacked / Longed for (variants: Loved / Wished) | 4Ls |
| Mad / Sad / Glad (variants: Frustrated / Concerned / Happy) | MSG |
| No match | CUSTOM |
 
**CUSTOM**: Treat each frame as a named bucket. Do not force-fit. If frame names
are opaque ("Group 1", unlabelled), treat the board as fully unstructured.
 
For multi-session input: detect format per session independently. A format change
across sessions is a coaching signal — note it in Dataset Overview.
 
Full variant mapping and edge cases: `references/format-detection.md`
 
