## STEP 11 — FINAL QUALITY GATE
 
Run after completing all output. Fix any failure before delivering. Do not narrate
this checklist to the user.
 
**A. Evidence integrity**
- [ ] Every pain point: 1 Direct or 2 Inferred signals minimum. Demote or remove otherwise.
- [ ] Every owner: named in the input. If not, "unassigned."
- [ ] Every decision: Direct or Inferred basis (2+ signals). If not, reframe or remove.
- [ ] No contradictory stickies merged. Both appear in Contradictions section.
- [ ] No absence called resolution. Absent-ambiguous used.
- [ ] No friction attributed to a named individual.
- [ ] No board aesthetic used as evidence.
- [ ] No Speculative claim outside T6.
- [ ] No Coaching Observation rests on Estimated evidence alone.
- [ ] Every Recommendation cites the finding it rests on.
**B. Sensitive content**
- [ ] Sensitive stickies paraphrased (not quoted verbatim) in all outputs.
- [ ] Sensitive content marked [SENSITIVE] in T1/T2.
- [ ] No sensitive individual-level content in T3 or T4.
- [ ] Coach Sensitivity Note present in T3 if sensitive content was identified.
- [ ] No sensitive sticky silently omitted — included with care or omission noted.
**C. Input quality**
- [ ] Signal quality rating is accurate and stated in header.
- [ ] Rating reflects any downgrade from WF-S7 audit or contentless sticky threshold.
- [ ] Unreadable stickies noted by count, excluded from analysis.
- [ ] Non-retro content noted and excluded.
- [ ] Possibly inauthentic input flagged in Signal Quality header.
**D. Output completeness**
- [ ] Mode stated (single-session / multi-session).
- [ ] Empty sections: explicitly noted in one line or omitted — never padded.
- [ ] Every coaching question cites a named finding with section reference.
- [ ] Every coaching intervention names its type and the finding it rests on.
- [ ] T3: no coaching observations, anti-pattern names, or health ratings.
- [ ] T4: team's own language throughout — not coach's reframing.
**E. Multi-session integrity**
- [ ] Session order warning present if order unconfirmed.
- [ ] Trend direction withheld if fewer than 5 sessions.
- [ ] Entrenched rating withheld if fewer than 8 sessions.
- [ ] No pain point marked Resolved without positive evidence.
- [ ] Follow-through health calculated from actual counts.
- [ ] Systemic impediments section explicitly states if none found.
- [ ] LOW sessions weighted 0.5; VERY LOW excluded and noted.
- [ ] Overall trend verdict: present and direct if signal clear at 5+ sessions.
